	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Cool.  Thanks.<br />I took a pin out and it's a 1.20mm round pin,,10mm long.<br /><br />We're you able to solder a paper clip?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>wyatt8740</b> [ Sat Sep 21, 2013 6:32 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: NES controller pin size?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Markfrizb wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Cool.  Thanks.<br />I took a pin out and it's a 1.20mm round pin,,10mm long.<br /><br />We're you able to solder a paper clip?</div><br />I cut it to a better length, fluxed it (may not be necessary, IDK) and, yeah, was able to solder it rather easily.<br /><br />I recommend a clip without the 'scoring' (cuts) on it, if you can find one of the right size. Apparently people have trouble finding those, but I got a box at a post office (or maybe it was UPS; can't remember which). I don't think a scored one would <em>hurt</em>, but it is easier to snap one of those accidentally.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


